The paper discusses the problem of vanishing gradients in recurrent neural networks, which is a common issue in the field of neural networks and falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also proposes a novel network architecture and compares its performance with other models, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper deals with sequence learning tasks, which is a common application of artificial intelligence and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of the model for question answering, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the model for image classification tasks, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
